<Author>COresident
<Content>Great service - bad location I stayed at the Villa Ixora in late October and got great rates due to the low season. In fact, I was the only one staying at the Villa while I was there.I stayed in a one-bedroom villa. It was very nicely furnished and immaculate. I was not crazy about the 1/2 outdoor bathroom, but that's more of a Bali thing than a Villa Ixora thing. Lots of mosquitos at night when you turn the light on.The service team is super friendly and very helpful. The pool is nice, but small, but not a problem when I was there as I had it to myself. The location was not great. It's about a 10-minute walk to the beach and it's not a beach you would want to swim at. And I agree that it's definitely a male prostitute pick up area. You really couldn't walk anywhere from the villa, so if that's a priority for you, I wouldn't recommend staying here. And if you just hang out by the pool all day, you could really be anywhere.So although the service was awesome and the facilities nice, I wouldn't recommend this place based solely on the location. But if hanging by a pool all day works for you, this might be the perfect place - especially for the price. 
