<Content>Wonderful Introduction to Bali My family and I stayed at Villa Ixora for seven nights in early June 2007. This was our very first trip to Bali and I must say that we were thoroughly impressed with the hospitality we received. The level of service from the staff members was always of a high standard. Titin (the villa manager) and BangBang (the driver) were always happy to assist us. Helmut (the owner) was quick to respond to my initial booking enquiry and, likewise, to any enquiries we had during our stay.The accommodation is very clean, the grounds are well kept and the swimming pool was clean and inviting. The breakfasts and afternoon teas were always amazing. We were spoilt with the freshly baked croissants, pastries, cakes and breads. On occasion we even had lunch on the premises and found the food to always be of high quality.Our children, 6 and 1.5yrs had a wonderful time. The staff were always happy to entertain them. They even befriended one of the staff member's little boys.It's definitely a place I would recommend to young families. 
