<Author>dkuta
<Content>Relaxing and exciting We knew about Ixora from Tripadvisor.We stayed there one week over New Year.We needed 4 double rooms for 8 adults and booked a two bedroom villa and two 1 bedroom units.Making the reservation I heard that they were building a second two bedroom villa, but were not sure it would be finished in time. It was finished and we were the second guests.The other villa is very nice with beautiful Indonesian furniture, very modern bathrooms partly open airand all other facilities you expect plus a private pool. The new one however is stunning.The owners have combined very succesfully old and new. An old teak structure with marvellous carvings, an old Joglo with Joglo roof, open air rain shower bathrooms with sunken bath, contemporary furniture combined with modern lighting, stainlees steel accessories, modern outdoor kitchen, a large oudoor livingterrace and pool deck and a large infinity pool just next to one of the bedrooms.The service, beds and covers, amminities, towels, staff friendliness, breakfast and the food was just very good.We were living in a quiet oasis, tropical garden and hardly felt the other guests.However it is just a stroll from beach and more importantly the in places in Seminyak and Legian. If you like to walk go to Living Room, Hu'u Restaurant and Bar,The Legian, Ku De Ta and many other places by foot in about 10-20 minutes.We are intending to book again with a larger group of 18 people to celebrate my birthday. They can accomodatein all units up to 20 guests in double rooms.This is an ideal place for a group of friends or larger family reunion, small wedding or similar events. 
