<Author>illeken
<Content>A lovely, cozy, friendly, beautiful resort in Bali We had lived many years in Singapore and visited Bali many times. Mostly we stayed in 5 or 4 Star hotels.This time a friend from Italy recommended Villa Ixora in Seminyak.We arrived in the evening in the airport and were received by a friendly lady staff from Villa Ixora. A short trip with one of the comfortable cars brought us in 25 minutes to the resort.It was dark but we could already see all the green trees, plants and flowers all iluminated with a lot of lamps. Not bright but light enough and it gave us a cozy feeling.Our room was surprisingly large, bigger than in many of the hotels we had visited before, with nice furniture, decorated with love, welcome flowers and having all facilities you need such as international TV, Mini Bar, small pantry and a very nice and clean bathroom with really white towels and not gray as experienced often before.The next morning we had a sumptious breakfast with all sort of home made breads, cold cuts, eggs in all styles, fruits and juices and more in the gazebo next to one of the pools.The owners were always there for us for planning a trip, shopping tips, restaurant tips from economical to luxurious and from meat to fish to Inodonesian dishes.We ha a very relaxing time and very often didn't go out for dinner but we choose from their menu or ordered some special food in the morning fish, prawns, lobster or other indonesian dishes such as Soto Ayam, Rendang, steamed fish chinese style or others.The staff is friendly, polite and always helpful.The beach is only a short stroll from the resort and the water is much cleaner than in Kuta. The beach is not crowded and one can walk hours along the sea.We will visit Bali next year again and will bring some friends and book one of their lovely villas with private pool and all other facilties to make a relaxing holiday really relaxing. 
