<Author>R&Rexpert
<Content>Outstanding Service AFter 10 years of living in Jakarta, I have been to Bali countless times and stayed in many places but mainly the expensive large, sea front hotels that cater to masses of people. This last time, on a friend's recommendation, I stayed for 8 restful days in Villa Ixora, Seminyak. I will never again stay in those huge non-personal hotels. Villa Ixora, owned and run by Helmut and Julia, was a delightful experience. The rooms are spacious, tastefully furnished and have a balcony or terrace. Bathrooms are excellent. Helmut says Villa Ixora Is not a restuarant but on the nights I didn't go out, I found the food served to be quite good. It is located close to many of Bali's top restuarants so there is no shortage of night entertainment close by. And the beach is only a short walk away. The property isstill surrounded by padi fields but at the rate villas are being built, this may not be the case for much longer.A highlight for me was the service. Nothing was too much trouble for the staff - or indeed Helmut and Julia. From the complimentary pick up at the airport, to borrowing Helmut's internet connection, to arranging motor bikes for guests or being invited to join the family clelbrations for Helmut's birthday. The service was attentive but unobtrusive. One morning I mentioned I would love to try one of Julia's cakes. For afternoon tea, individual chocolate mousse cakes covered in coconut appeared in the room. Julia has a separate business supplying amazing cakes for hotels, restuarants and weddings. Breakfasts, included in the room rate, were excellent with a variety of home made breads offered. Requests for items not on the menu were always accommodated. And breakfast is served ... whenever you want it. Perfect for holidays! At the risk of making this place too popular, I would highly recommend Villa Ixora for anyone who wants peace and quiet for their vacation but within easy reach of night life. 
